m_dot_crah = cfg.crah_nominal_airflow_kgs * fan_speeds   # (n_crahs,)
So ṁ_zone = 65 kg/s × fan_speed_fraction. At the default 85% fan speed, that's ~55 kg/s per zone; at 100% it's 65 kg/s; at the 10% floor it's 6.5 kg/s. Whenever a controller changes fan speed (heuristic, PID, or RL action), the zone airflow changes immediately on the next step.

At the individual rack level
Within a zone, airflow is distributed proportionally to each rack's power, not equally:

python
